===============================================================================

PgTriggers has been installed!

Next steps:

1. Run migrations:
   $ rails db:migrate

2. Mount the engine in your routes.rb (already done):
   mount PgTriggers::Engine => "/pg_triggers"

3. Configure the gem in config/initializers/pg_triggers.rb

4. Create your first trigger:

   # In app/triggers/example_trigger.rb
   PgTriggers::DSL.pg_trigger "example_guard" do
     table :users
     on :insert, :update
     function :validate_user_rules
     version 1
     enabled false
     when_env :production
   end

5. Visit http://localhost:3000/pg_triggers to access the UI

For more information, see: https://github.com/samaswin87/pg_triggers

===============================================================================
